@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Simonize' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
4 colours.

                             How to play?

  When first run, 'Simonize' displays the main menu where you can
choose the game board size and the game speed. When you are ready
to play, click on the 'Play!' button.

  For each game board size and game speed, the 'Best sequence' and
its associated best number of moves is displayed on top in the
window.

  Playing the game is very simple: 'Simonize' will briefly highlight
a sequence of 3 tiles, and it's up to you to click on the right
tiles, in the same order. If you are successful, the game will
highlight those same tiles plus a new one and so on.

  Have fun!

                                 OPTIONS

  In the main menu there are the following buttons:

 @{b}About@{ub}         - Displays the informations about the game.

 @{b}5 x 5...9 x 9@{ub} - Lets you choose the board size you want to
                 play with.

 @{b}Slow/Fast@{ub}     - For selecting the game speed (how much time
                 each tile will stay highlighted).

 @{b}Play!@{ub}         - To play the game.

NOTE: When playing, you can go back anytime to the main menu by
      clicking on the window's close button.

